narratives.question_text: What knowledge, skills, and insights did you develop by taking this course?
comments: Learned about AI and machine learning usefulness in different fields and how to study datasets
Learning a ton about data ethics. Elisa is a great resource to have in your undergraduate career if you are interested in data, S&DS, or ethics generally.
I learned about the ways that biases in statistics and algorithms can have grave consequences, as well as some of the ways that these consequences have been combatted/ might be combatted.

narratives.question_text: What are the strengths and weaknesses of this course and how could it be improved?
comments:
Strengths - open discussion format, lots of room for conversation and learning 
Weakness - readings were unclear and not posted regularly

Strengths: Readings were solid, Low workload, Low intensity, Interesting Final Paper Topic Ideas and Conversations
Weaknesses: Class structure felt unguided at times.
Strengths: Interesting readings, final project was very open-ended, work load very reasonable, prof knowledgeable and understanding

narratives.question_text: Would you recommend this course to another student? Please explain.
comments: Yes, if looking for a lowkey stem class that investigates the ethics behind data science and if you like readings and discussing
Yes I would! The class was pretty fun and I learned a lot. It was nice as a fifth class.
